\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s9\qj\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe1033\hich\f5\fs20\lang1033\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s9\qj\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe1033\hich\f5\fs20\lang1033\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i\b0{\*\cs28\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\i\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i Reader:}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0  {\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 20.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Adam gave names to all the cattle and to all the birds of the sky, and to all the wild beasts of the field, but for Adam there was not found a help like unto himself. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 21.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And God brought a trance upon Adam, and he slept, and he took one of 
his ribs, and filled up the flesh instead thereof. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 22.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And God formed the rib which he took from Adam into a woman, and brought her to Adam. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 23.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Adam said, This now is bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh; she shall be called woman, because she was 
taken out of her husband. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 24.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Therefore shall a man leave his father, and his mother and shall cleave to his wife, and they two shall be one flesh. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 1.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the two were naked both Adam and his wife, and were not ashamed. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 2.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Now the serpent was the most craf
ty of all the brutes on the earth, which the Lord God made, and the serpent said to the woman, Wherefore has God said, Eat not of every tree of the garden? }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 3.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the woman said to the serpent, We may eat of the fruit of the trees of the garden, }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 4.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  but of 
the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, God said ye shall not eat of it, neither shall ye touch it, lest ye die. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 5.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the serpent said to the woman, ye shall not surely die. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 6.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  For God knew that in whatever day ye should eat of it your
 eyes would be opened, and ye would be as gods, knowing good and evil. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 7.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was pleasant to the eyes to look upon and beautiful to contemplate and having taken of its fruit she ate, and she gave 
to her husband also with her, and they ate. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 8.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the eyes of both were opened, and they perceived that they were naked, and they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves aprons to go round them. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 9.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And they heard the voice of the Lord God walking in
 the garden in the afternoon; and both Adam and his wife hid themselves from the face of the Lord God in the midst of the trees of the garden. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 10.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the Lord God called Adam and said to him, Adam, where art thou? }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 11.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And he said to him, I heard thy voice
 as thou walkedst in the garden, and I feared because I was naked and I hid myself. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 12.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And God said to him, Who told thee that thou wast naked, unless thou hast eaten of the tree concerning which I charged thee of it alone not to eat? }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 13.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Adam said, t
he woman whom thou gavest to be with me -- she gave me of the tree and I ate. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 14.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the Lord God said to the woman, why hast thou done this? And the woman said, the serpent deceived me and I ate. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 15.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the Lord God said to the serpent, Because thou has
t done this thou art cursed above all cattle and all the brutes of the earth on thy breast and belly thou shalt go, and thou shalt eat earth all the days of thy life. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 16.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And I will put enmity between thee and the woman and between thy seed and her seed, h
e shall watch against thy head, and thou shalt watch against his heel. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 17.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And to the woman he said, I will greatly multiply thy pains and thy groanings; in pain thou shalt bring forth children, and thy submission shall be to thy husband, and he shall rule
 over thee. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 18.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And to Adam he said, Because thou hast hearkened to the voice of thy wife, and eaten of the tree concerning which I charged thee of it only not to eat -- of that thou hast eaten, cursed is the ground in thy labors, in pain shalt thou eat of
 it all the days of thy life. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 19.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Thorns and thistles shall it bring forth to thee, and thou shalt eat the herb of the field. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 20.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  In the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat thy bread until thou return to the earth out of which thou wast taken, for earth thou 
art and to earth thou shalt return. }}
