\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s9\qj\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe1033\hich\f5\fs20\lang1033\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s9\qj\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe1033\hich\f5\fs20\lang1033\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i\b0{\*\cs28\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\i\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i Reader:}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0  {\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 19.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  God by wisdom founded the earth, and by prudence he prepared the heavens. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 20.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  By understanding were the depths broken up, and the clouds dropped water. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 21.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  My son, let them not pass from thee, but keep my counsel and understanding: }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 22.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  that thy
 soul may live, and that there may be grace round thy neck; and it shall be health to thy flesh, and safety to thy bones: }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 23.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  that thou mayest go confidently in peace in all thy ways, and that thy foot may not stumble. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 24.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  For if thou rest, thou shalt be u
ndismayed; and if thou sleep, thou shalt slumber sweetly. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 25.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And thou shalt not be afraid of alarm coming upon thee, neither of approaching attacks of ungodly men. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 26.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  For the Lord shall be over all thy ways, and shall establish thy foot that thou be not 
moved. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 27.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Forbear not to do good to the poor, whensoever thy hand may have power to help him. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 28.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Say not, Come back another time, to-morrow I will give; while thou art able to do him good: for thou knowest not what the next day will bring forth. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 29.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Devi
se not evil against thy friend, living near thee and trusting in thee. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 30.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Be not ready to quarrel with a man without a cause, lest he do thee some harm. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 31.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Procure not the reproaches of bad men, neither do thou covet their ways. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 32.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  For every transgresso
r is unclean before the Lord; neither does he sit among the righteous. 33 .The curse of God is in the houses of the ungodly; but the habitations of the just are blessed. }{\*\cs30\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033\rtlch\ltrch\hich\fs16\loch\fs16 34.}{\*\cs24\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The Lord resists the proud; but he gives grace to the humble. }}
